{"id":"hezron-1","term":"Hezron (1)","source":"International Standard Bible Encyclopaedia (James Orr ed., 1915)","html":"<p>hez'-ron (chetsron, and chetsron; Septuagint Asron):</p><p>(1) A son of Reuben (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 46:9\">Ge 46:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 6:14\">Ex 6:14</a>), and head of the family of the Hezronites (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 26:6\">Nu 26:6</a>).</p><p>(2) A son of Perez, and grandson of Judah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 46:12\">Ge 46:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 26:21\">Nu 26:21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 2:5\">1Ch 2:5</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 2:9\">9</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 2:18\">18</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 2:21\">21</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 2:24\">24</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 2:25\">25</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 4:1\">4:1</a>), a direct ancestor of David (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ruth 4:18\">Ru 4:18</a> f). He appears also in the genealogy of our Lord (Esrom) (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 1:3\">Mt 1:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 3:33\">Lu 3:33</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 46:9","Exodus 6:14","Numbers 26:6","Genesis 46:12","Numbers 26:21","1 Chronicles 2:5","1 Chronicles 2:9","1 Chronicles 2:18","1 Chronicles 2:21","1 Chronicles 2:24","1 Chronicles 2:25","1 Chronicles 4:1","Ruth 4:18","Matthew 1:3","Luke 3:33"]}